Using the spoolie, comb through eyebrows to groom into shape and see the sparse areas that need filling. Twist up the retractable pencil and fill in gaps using small hair-like strokes in the direction of your natural hair growth. For the inner corner of the brow, closest to the bridge of the nose, apply the pencil very lightly for a soft, barely-there application. Once brows are filled in, use the spoolie again to soften the colour for a realistic, natural brow effect. For extra definition and lift, apply more strokes of colour to the arch and tail of the brow. Pair with an Eyeko Brow Gel to lock hairs in place.

Directions from packaging:
Using the spoolie, comb through eyebrows to groom into shape and see the sparse areas that need filling. Twist up the retractable pencil and fill in gaps using small hair-like strokes in the direction of your natural hair growth. For the inner corner of the brow, closest to the bridge of the nose, apply the pencil very lightly for a soft, barely-there application. Once brows are filled in, use the spoolie again to soften the colour for a realistic, natural brow effect. For extra definition and lift, apply more strokes of colour to the arch and tail of the brow. Pair with an Eyeko Brow Gel to lock hairs in place.

Label:

Directions from packaging:
Using the spoolie, comb through eyebrows to groom into shape and see the sparse areas that need filling. Twist up the retractable pencil and fill in gaps using small hair-like strokes in the direction of your natural hair growth. For the inner corner of the brow, closest to the bridge of the nose, apply the pencil very lightly for a soft, barely-there application. Once brows are filled in, use the spoolie again to soften the colour for a realistic, natural brow effect. For extra definition and lift, apply more strokes of colour to the arch and tail of the brow. Pair with an Eyeko Brow Gel to lock hairs in place.
